5:
How about a coffee? Afraid all we've
got is the synthetic stuff, though.
9:
Sure, thanks. Anything's better than
AdTaste.
13:
This is quite the treat, having some
one-on-one time with you.
17:
Let me guess... Wedding bells are
finally ringing for you and Nate? Just
say the word, I'd be happy to broach
the subject with her parents for you!
22:
If that was it, we'd be here together...
I'm here to ask you what you know
about this data.
27:
Ahh, that case takes me WAY back.
What, were you doing some spring
cleaning in your data reserves?
30:
About ten years ago, AltMeme went
through a full-scale restructuring
after a huge scandal came to light.
And, PBC was founded around the
same time.
32:
But as for the case file... Your name
happens to be at the top of the
suspect list.
36:
Ah, I see. It's a little late for an
interrogation, don't you think?
40:
Tell me, King Johnson... What is it
you're after, really?
43:
Judging by the evidence here, it
appears that founding PBC came at
quite the cost...
46:
Yet you sacrificed all that you had
gained so easily for Nate and
Stinelle. What's the catch?
50:
I hope you aren't insinuating that I'm
using the two of them for personal
gain.
54:
As a hero and a role model, it is my
duty to pave the way forward for
young girls like them.
58:
And there's no doubt about it. Nate
got her biggest break when she met
you and Alk. She's lucky to have you.
63:
That combat frame... Was it from
your days as a troubleshooter?
68:
You like it, do you? CEOs as suave as
this don't come around too often!
72:
Mind indulging me and listening to a
tale from my glory days?
75:
This is a story of two
mischievous—not to mention
devilishly handsome—upstarts.
80:
Bwahaha! Fell for it, huh King?! Did
you really think I'd just run away?!
86:
Shame. This job's gonna be over
before it even gets interesting.
89:
Grgh... Don't just stand there, you
idiots! Kill him!
101:
This will be the last time you
underestimate King Johnson.
105:
Bring ten times the firepower next
time if you want to stand a chance.
111:
Looking good out there, King! Sorry,
was that job a little too easy for you?
113:
Don't you have some work to do,
Betrane?
117:
I'm hard at work as we speak! Just
hacked into their network for some
juicy new info—including the target's
location and the coordinates of their
hideout!
121:
Amateurs. You'd think AltMeme
would know how to protect their
data better, eh?
125:
Then hand over the details already.
I'll move in on their location.
129:
All right, geez! Patience is a virtue,
you know.
133:
...Got it. Take care of the data
backup for me.
137:
Yup! Just try not to blow up the
target while you're at it.
144:
Beautiful work out there, King! I'd
expect nothing less.
148:
The data hand-off isn't until
tomorrow. Don't let your guard down.
152:
Lighten up a bit, will ya? We're
practically done. I'd say it's time for
a drink!
156:
Cheers. To a soon-to-be job well
done.
161:
And to the success of your
soon-to-be company!
164:
Once this job is finished, you'll have
enough money for your start-up...
Heh. "CEO King Johnson," what a
concept.
172:
Oh, just that a grumpy, arrogant,
lone wolf like you would end up as
the head of a company. A guy can't
help but be in awe of it all.
176:
It wouldn't kill you to laugh now and
again, y'know! CEOs need to be
personable. C'mon, give me a little
smile!
183:
I'm here to do a job. All that matters
is that the job gets done. I'll leave
the smiling to you.
187:
What am I, your mother? You've got
aaall this potential... and yet you still
want me to handle everything for
you.
191:
You're good with client relations. It's
a simple matter of dividing labor.
195:
Heh, fine by me. I'll just do my part
and keep the jobs coming. But for
now...
198:
Aren't you curious about what kinda
data we've got our hands on here?
207:
Not even a little bit? C'mon, they're
paying a fortune for this!
210:
For a gigantic corporation like
AltMeme to be throwing a fortune at
troubleshooters to steal their data
back... this must be some SENSITIVE
stuff.
214:
Work is work. Who said I have to
care about the contents of the data
I handle?
218:
...You've changed, King. There was a
time when you would've opened this
up in a heartbeat. Now look at you.
Yawwwn.
222:
Not my fault. You're the one who
picked this job, Betrane.
226:
That's precisely why I'm
disappointed. I crave adventure,
King.
229:
...Are you seriously not gonna look at
it? You're no fun.
233:
I'll be on top of the world soon
enough. What could be more fun
than that?
237:
Man, you really do have a CEO's
discipline... You won't bite—even with
a delicious-looking treat balanced
on your nose.
241: What am I, some mutt? Knock it off.
245:
Ten-four, buddy. I can't force you to
look, so I guess I'll just shut my trap
until the job's done.
248:
You know as well as I do that life's
too short to not enjoy it. Kind of a
waste to hold back too much,
y'know?
261: Is that how you see it, Betrane?
